We can assert the answer must be in [1, len + 1], the len is the length of input array. Because if the answer is greater than len + 1, then [1, 2, ...., len + 1] must be in the array, but the array of len length only can store [1, 2, ..., len]. 
So, first we can replace the zero or negative with len + 1, and that not change answer. then this problem similar with [find-all-numbers-disappeared-in-an-array](https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-numbers-disappeared-in-an-array/), [find-all-duplicates-in-an-array](https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-duplicates-in-an-array/) :)
```
class Solution {
    public int firstMissingPositive(int[] nums) {
        int len = nums.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            if (nums[i] <= 0) {
                nums[i] = len + 1;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            int n = Math.abs(nums[i]);
            if (n <= len && nums[n - 1] > 0) {
                nums[n - 1] *= -1;
            }
        }

        int first = len + 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            if (nums[i] >= 0) {
                first = i + 1;
                break;
            }
        }

        return first;
    }
}
