Solution Approach- Try placing the number at position where index and value can be equal. such that i= nums[i]-1 (zero based index)
```
// Time-O(N), Space-O(1)
	public static int firstMissingPositive(int[] nums) {
		if (nums == null || nums.length == 0) {
			return -1;
		}

		int n = nums.length;
		int i = 0;
		while (i < n) {
			// if number is either less than 1 or already at the right position skip it
			if (nums[i] < 1 || nums[i] == i + 1) {
				i++;
			} else {
				// don't increment i here, we can compare again after its value is updated
				// if number is beyond array size then change to out of range (-1)
				if (nums[i] > n) {
					nums[i] = -1;
				} else {
					// number being swapped already matches, don't swap to avoid infinite loops [1,1]
					if (nums[i] == nums[nums[i] - 1]) {
						i++;
					} else {
						// swap to make sure value of nums[i] can be placed to its desired position (if value is 4, place it at the 4th index- i=3)
						int temp = nums[nums[i] - 1];
						nums[nums[i] - 1] = nums[i];
						nums[i] = temp;
					}
				}
			}
		}

		// scan to see if number is not at its desired position, that position is the result
		for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
			if (nums[j] != j + 1) {
				return j + 1;
			}
		}

		// if every number is at its desired position then size+1 is the answer
		return n + 1;
	}
```

