solutions.content:
# Intuition
The constraints for node->val are from -10^5 to 10^5. Simply change the value out of this range so that we will know if we visited that node or not.

# Approach
First we iterate the list untill we get null. First we check if `val == -100001`. `-100001` (say `bignum`) is just a number outside the constraints bounds. If the node val is equal to bignum then that means the node is already visites so we `return true` because cycle is there. 
Else we change the value to bignum and go to the next node. After few iteration if any node val == bignum that means we already visited that node so cycle is present. 
If we get out of that loop that means we didnot visit the same node twice, so no cycle is present so we `return false`. 

`bignum` can be any number outside the range `-10^5 to 10^5`

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
- Space complexity: O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasCycle(ListNode *head) {     
        while(head)
        {
            if(head->val == -100001) return true;
            head->val = -100001;
            head = head->next;
        }
        return false;
    }
};
```

