This problem uses famous Tortoise-Haire Algorithm.
Here slowPointer is Tortoise and FastPointer is Haire.
While Tortoise moves one step at a time, Haire moves 2 steps at a time, so it should reach end earlier than tortoise.
But in any case, they both meet, that means there is a cycle present.
**O(N) Time, O(1) Space**
