solutions.content:
Iterate over all characters.
When you encounter an operation, perform the method(recursion) on the left side, then perform on the right side as well(recursion).
Combine the each value from the left list to each value of the right list using the operation encountered before.
return the collected values.
Base case: there is no operation detected in the provided substring, return the number.
Memo: save the lists on the memo before returning and check before doing the recursion.
```
class Solution {

    List<Integer>[][] memo;
    public List<Integer> diffWaysToCompute(String expression) {
        memo = new List[expression.length()][expression.length()];
        return diffWaysToCompute(0,expression.length()-1,expression);
    }
    public List<Integer> diffWaysToCompute(int index1, int index2, String expression){
        if(memo[index1][index2]!=null) return memo[index1][index2];
        ArrayList<Integer> answers = new ArrayList<>();
        boolean hasOperation = false;
        for(int i = index1; i <=index2; i++){
            char c = expression.charAt(i);
            if(c<48){
                hasOperation=true;
                List<Integer> left = diffWaysToCompute(index1,i-1,expression);
                List<Integer> right = diffWaysToCompute(i+1,index2,expression);
                for(int l: left){
                    for(int r: right){
//                        System.out.format("%d, %d %n",l,r);
                        switch(c){
                            case '+'-> answers.add(l+r);
                            case '*'-> answers.add(l*r);
                            case '-'-> answers.add(l-r);
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        if(!hasOperation){
            int num = 0;
            for(int i = index1; i<=index2; i++){
                num = num*10+(expression.charAt(i)-48);
            }
            answers.add(num);
        }
        memo[index1][index2] = answers;
        return answers;
    }

}
```

