**Idea** : Idea is to partition the string into two parts whenever we find binary operator and now solve the question for smaller problem, that is Greedy approach . This process keep going until we hit a string of length = 1, our base case. 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/32044bb6-bdcb-4dab-b30f-39702f7a73a3_1609571948.149371.png)
Image credit goes to [Codebix](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZJRtZh8O6FKWH49YLapAbQ)

```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> diffWaysToCompute(String input) {

        //Base case
        if(input.length()==1){
            List<Integer>temp = new ArrayList<>();
            int num = input.charAt(0)-'0';
            temp.add(num);
            return temp;
        }
        List<Integer>ans = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0;i<input.length();i++){

            //If there is a binary operator, then partition
            if(input.charAt(i)=='+'||input.charAt(i)=='-'||input.charAt(i)=='*'){
                String p1 = input.substring(0,i);
                String p2 = input.substring(i+1);

                List<Integer>res1 = diffWaysToCompute(p1);
                List<Integer>res2 = diffWaysToCompute(p2);

				//Now compute values using both parts
                for(int t1 : res1){
                    for(int t2 : res2){
                        if(input.charAt(i)=='+'){
                            ans.add(t1+t2);
                        }else if(input.charAt(i)=='-'){
                            ans.add(t1-t2);
                        }else {
                            ans.add(t1*t2);
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        //Means there is no operator in Input string, that's why ans list is empty
        if(ans.size()==0)ans.add(Integer.valueOf(input));
        return ans;

    }
}
```

**Note** : I didn't use DP because it was already showing 99% faster solution, so, I didn't apply DP. Though DP can be applied using HashMap and then it will become more faster.

