If you know about the Tabulation DP approach of MCM, you will get this easily.
In MCM, for ```[mat[i],..,mat[j]]```, we try all type of multiplication possible, and take the minimum.

Here I am maintaining vector for each ```dp[i][j]``` cell, all possible evaluation for ```[i,...,j]``` operands.
So instead of taking minimum from all the subproblems, i am crossproducting vectors of ```dp[i][k] and dp[i][k+1] for all i <= k < j```. crossproduct has operator ```operators[k]``` from actual expression.

So, 1. Divide given expression into operands and operator vector
2. Apply above given logic
3. Look at the ```function crossproduct()```  for details on how cross product been taken.

