**Note**
For an enumerable type (e.g., Array, List, etc.), we can use enumerator to retrieve its values. We can use ```GetEnumerator()``` to get the enumerator.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/15e13163-073d-4cae-88b8-eb464f5cffcc_1633734350.3798525.png)

The ```Enumerator``` implements the ```IEnumerator``` interface, which contains 3 members: ```Current```, ```MoveNext()``` and ```Reset()```.
- ```Current```: property that returns the element at the current position of the enumrator.
- ```MoveNext()```: move to the next element.
- ```Reset()```: set enumerator to its initial position.


**Implementation**
```
public class NestedIterator {

    public Stack<IEnumerator<NestedInteger>> stack;

    public NestedIterator(IList<NestedInteger> nestedList) {

        stack = new Stack<IEnumerator<NestedInteger>>();
        stack.Push(nestedList.GetEnumerator());
    }

    public bool HasNext() {

        while(stack.Count > 0)
        {
            if(stack.Peek().MoveNext())
            {
                if(stack.Peek().Current.IsInteger())
                    return true;
                else
                    stack.Push(stack.Peek().Current.GetList().GetEnumerator());
            }
            else
                stack.Pop();
        }

        return false;
    }

    public int Next() {

        return stack.Peek().Current.GetInteger();
    }
}
```

