**Explaination of Functions :**

* **Flatten** : There are 2 possibilities at every level. One is diretly integer insert it directly to the vector. Otherwise call the same fuction to separate the integer ans list.

* **NestedIterator** : Iterate for every element and nested list through our flatten function and also keep on incresing the counter value for the size of flatten vector.

* **Next** : Next function will return the next value 

* **HasNext** : HasNext will return false if our next function reached the vector size otherwise true.

```
class NestedIterator {
public:

    int m=0,n=0;
    vector<int> flatten;

    void flatten(NestedInteger x){

        if(x.isInteger())
            flatten.push_back(x.getInteger());
        else {
            for(auto i:x.getList())
                flatten(i);
        }
    }

    NestedIterator(vector<NestedInteger> &a) {
        for(auto i:a)
            flatten(i);
        n = flatten.size();
    }

    int next() {
        m++;
        return flatten[m-1];
    }

    bool hasNext() {
        if(m==n)
            return false;//reached capacity!
        return true;
    }
};
```

